						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the Pārvati shrine in the compound of Madhukēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Sadāśivarājēndra]—16th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Nandana, Vasanta, Monday,</hi> the details being not verifiable. It is in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">16th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records that the stone <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Pārvati shrine was an offering of <hi rend="bold">Sadās11iva-rājēndra of Sōde.</hi> </p>						

